      "side": 1,
      "message": "Two thoughts:\n1) Do we think this could fail with other control-flow (eg, do-while or if-else)?\n2) It\u0027s still silly, (slightly less so), but you could write:\n    for (int i \u003d 0; i \u003c 10; ++i) float unused \u003d function_with_side_effects();\n  ... should we just be forcing scopes on loop bodies all the time, instead?",
      "revId": "51d11ee42fc8d1dd43ce26328d03d54434cb03c5",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
