      "writtenOn": "2021-03-04T16:21:54Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "1) Do-while and if-else already disallow this: see errors/UnscopedVariableInDoWhile.sksl, UnscopedVariableInIf.sksl, UnscopedVariableInElse.sksl. The only reason we allowed it for `for` at all is that they naturally have a SymbolTable.\n\n2) There\u0027s no reason to write it this way instead of \n    for (int i \u003d 0; i \u003c 10; ++i) function_with_side_effects();\nor\n    for (int i \u003d 0; i \u003c 10; ++i) { float unused\u003dfunction_with_side_effects(); }\n\nWe could just arbitrarily inject {} around loops, sure, but I would be worried that this would leak into our round-trips, e.g. code going through Pipeline would start getting a silly number of extra braces.\n\nGiven that this has never come up before except in this weird synthetic example,  Android doesn\u0027t allow it, and SkSL doesn\u0027t allow it for similar control-flow structures, I don\u0027t think we need to support it.",
      "parentUuid": "f2fbbf58_01312772",
